Denver and other cities along Colorado's Front Range cannot continue to provide adequate supplies of this vital resource. There is not enough water - naturally provided - in this region for the population size. In truth, Colorado's population growth has over-stressed water resources. In the near term, the cost of providing clean water to the populous will inhibit continued population growth.
